excluded from the academy of American letters. Finally here is a book that presents a solid portrait of a major artistic innovator, a writer who combines aesthetics and politics and who can perform as anthropologist, social goad, or media icon, all with consummate skill.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAmerican. 4aGeneral. 4aLiterary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aMurphy, Timothy S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052020951040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091940240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520919402423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520919402/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles